Food and drink contain the standard functions for any object
(wizhelp 4.6).  Instead of inheriting OBJECT, however, they
use the following:

DRINK - single serving of alcohol
FOOD - single serving of food
GEN_KEG - multiple servings of alcohol
GEN_MEAL - multiple servings of food

They also have additional functions, as follows:

Drink:
set_soft_strength(int)
    Determines how filling a drink is.  The total of soft plus
    alco strengths should be proportional to the total of hp
    plus sp healing.  Only single servings currently use this.

set_alco_strength(int)
set_strength(int)
    Determines how drunk the drink will make the character.

set_hp_healing(int)
set_hp_heal(int)
    Set the amount of hp healed.

set_sp_healing(int)
set_sp_heal(int)
    Set the amount of sp healed.

set_healing(int)
    Set both hp and sp healing to int.

query_full()
    Returns 1 if the bottle is full, 0 otherwise.

query_drinker_level()
    Returns the real level necessary to drink the drink.
    (Remember that bards and halflings will be able to drink
    it earlier.)

set_drinking_message(string)
    Sets the message others see when the character drinks.
    Can be left at the default in most cases.  Not used
    for jugs and kegs.

set_drinker_message(string)
set_drinker_mess(string)
    Sets the message the character sees when he drinks.
    set_drinker_message is preferred; set_drinker_mess is
    preserved for backward compatibility, but works only
    with drinks, not with kegs/jugs.

set_empty_container(string)
    Determines what the container is.  Defaults to "bottle".
    Does not apply to jugs or kegs.

set_stopper(string)
    Sets the string the character sees if his level is
    too low to drink.

set_drink_name(string)
    Sets the name of the drink, used in some default
    messages.

Kegs and jugs also use the following:
set_kind(<"keg"|"jug">)
    Determines whether the drink is in a keg or a jug.

set_max_drinks(int)
    Sets the maximum number of drinks that can be
    held.  The default should be used, unless the item
    is a special case for some reason.

set_drinks(int)
    Sets the number of drinks currently in the
    container, so you can clone up (for instance) a
    half-empty keg.

Food:
set_food_name(string)
    Sets the name of the food, used in some default
    messages.

reset_short(string)
    Use this instead of set_short in food, due to a
    peculiarity of inn food code.

set_eater_message(string)
set_eater_mess(string)
    Sets the message the character sees when he eats the
    food.  set_eater_message is preferred; set_eater_mess
    is preserved for backward compatibility but does not
    work with snacks and meals.

set_hp_heal(int)
    Sets the amount of hp healed by the food.

set_sp_heal(int)
    Sets the amount of sp healed by the food.

set_strength(int)
    Sets how full the food will make the character.  Should
    normally be about half of the total healing.  If hp_heal
    and/or sp_heal are not set, this also sets them to int.

Meals and snacks also use the following:
set_kind(<"snack"|"meal">)
    Set whether the item is a snack or a meal.

set_max_uses(int)
    Sets the maximum number of times the food could be
    eaten.  This should normally default, unless
    the item is special for some reason.

set_uses(int)
    Sets the number of times the food can be eaten,
    so you can clone up (for instance) a half-eaten
    meal.
